3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking): The paper focuses on a communication system and its performance analysis, which is a core area of communication and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The proposed system involves multiple nodes and requires proper management of interference, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): Although not the primary focus of the paper, the proposed system may have security implications, which falls under the scope of cryptography and security.
